    "display_name": "City Explorer",
    "long_instructions": "## **Do This**\r\n\r\n<br/> 1. **Choose a key user task.**\r\nThink about something a visitor might do on a city explorer web app, such as:\r\n\r\n* Browse local events or attractions\r\n* View details about a specific place or activity\r\n* Save something to their favorites list\r\n\r\n<br/> 2. **Trace the path.**\r\nOn your site map, show the pages a user would move through to complete that task.\r\n\r\n* Use **arrows or labels** to mark each click or page change.\r\n* Or write out the steps as a short list (e.g., *Home → Events → Event Details → Favorites*).\r\n\r\n<br/> 3. **Peer-test it.**\r\nPair up with another student:\r\n\r\n* One person plays the **user**, describing what they'd click.\r\n* The other follows along on the site map.\r\n* Notice where the user gets lost or repeats steps.\r\n",
    "bubble_choice_description": "Use your site map to explore how people navigate a city discovery web app.",
